25/******** IR Module ********/

27const PrimFuncNode* GetRootPrimFunc(const IRModule& mod, const StmtNode* root_block,
28 GlobalVar* result_g_var) {
29 for (const auto& kv : mod->functions) {
30 const GlobalVar& g_var = kv.first;
31 const BaseFunc& base_func = kv.second;
32 if (const auto* func = base_func.as<PrimFuncNode>()) {
33 if (const auto* realize = func->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
34 if (realize->block.get() == root_block) {
35 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
36 *result_g_var = g_var;
37 }
38 return func;
39 }
40 }
41 }
42 }
43 LOG(FATAL) << "IndexError: Could not get the corresponding function in the schedule state of the "
44 "statement:\n"
45 << GetRef<Stmt>(root_block);
46 throw;
47}
48
49const PrimFuncNode* FindEntryFunc(const IRModule& mod, GlobalVar* result_g_var) {
50 GlobalVar result = NullValue<GlobalVar>();
51 // Priority 1: PrimFunc marked as `tir::attr::kIsEntryFunc`
52 int num_prim_func = 0;
53 const tir::PrimFuncNode* main_func = nullptr;
54 const tir::PrimFuncNode* last_func = nullptr;
55 for (const auto& kv : mod->functions) {
56 GlobalVar gv = kv.first;
57 BaseFunc base_func = kv.second;
58 if (const auto* func = base_func.as<tir::PrimFuncNode>()) {
59 last_func = func;
60 if (func->HasNonzeroAttr(tir::attr::kIsEntryFunc)) {
61 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
62 *result_g_var = gv;
63 }
64 return func;
65 }
66 if (gv->name_hint == "main") {
67 main_func = func;
68 result = gv;
69 }
70 ++num_prim_func;
71 }
72 }
73 // Priority 2: PrimFunc whose name is `main`
74 if (main_func != nullptr) {
75 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
76 *result_g_var = result;
77 }
78 return main_func;
79 }
80 // Priority 3: The only PrimFunc in the IRModule
81 if (num_prim_func == 1) {
82 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
83 *result_g_var = result;
84 }
85 return last_func;
86 }
87 return nullptr;
88}

92StmtSRef GetScopeRoot(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& sref,
93 bool require_stage_pipeline) {
94 class RootBlockError : public ScheduleError {
95 public:
96 explicit RootBlockError(IRModule mod) : mod_(mod) {}
97 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
98 String FastErrorString() const final {
99 return "ScheduleError: The primitive does not operate on the root block";
100 }
101 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
102 return "The primitive does not operate on the root block";
103 }
104 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {}; }
105 IRModule mod_;
106 };
107
108 class NotStagePipelineError : public ScheduleError {
109 public:
110 explicit NotStagePipelineError(IRModule mod, Block block) : mod_(mod), block_(block) {}
111 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
112 String FastErrorString() const final {
113 return "ScheduleError: The scope root is not a stage pipeline";
114 }
115 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
116 return R"(The scope {0} is not a stage pipeline.
117Definition of a scope that is a stage pipeline:
118- The region cover property holds for every of its child blocks
119- No write-after-read dependency or opaque dependency,
120- only read-after-write and write-after-write are allowed
121- All the statements in the scope are schedulable statements, i.e. Block and For
122)";
123 }
124 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
125 IRModule mod_;
126 Block block_;
127 };
128
129 StmtSRef scope_root_sref{nullptr};
130 StmtSRef scope_root_subtree{nullptr};
131 // Step 1. Find the scope root and the subtree that the given sref is in
132 {
133 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref->parent;
134 const StmtSRefNode* subtree = sref.get();
135 for (; p != nullptr; subtree = p, p = p->parent) {
136 if (p->stmt->IsInstance<BlockNode>()) {
137 scope_root_sref = GetRef<StmtSRef>(p);
138 scope_root_subtree = GetRef<StmtSRef>(subtree);
139 break;
140 }
141 }
142 if (p == nullptr) {
143 throw RootBlockError(self->mod);
144 }
145 }
146 // Step 2. Handle `require_stage_pipeline`
147 if (require_stage_pipeline) {
148 bool stage_pipeline = self->GetBlockInfo(scope_root_sref).scope->stage_pipeline;
149 if (stage_pipeline == false) {
150 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_root_sref);
151 throw NotStagePipelineError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block));
152 }
153 }
154 return scope_root_sref;
155}
156
157ScopeBlockLoopInfo GetScopeBlockLoopInfo(const Block& scope_block) {
158 struct Collector : public StmtVisitor {
159 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* realize) final {
160 result.realizes.push_back(GetRef<BlockRealize>(realize));
161 const Array<IterVar>& iter_vars = realize->block->iter_vars;
162 const Array<PrimExpr>& iter_values = realize->iter_values;
163 ICHECK_EQ(iter_vars.size(), iter_values.size());
164 int n = realize->iter_values.size();
165 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
166 const IterVar& iter_var = iter_vars[i];
167 const PrimExpr& iter_value = iter_values[i];
168 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* vars = nullptr;
169 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
170 vars = &result.spatial_vars;
171 } else {
172 vars = &result.non_spatial_vars;
173 }
174 PostOrderVisit(iter_value, [vars](const ObjectRef& obj) {
175 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
176 vars->insert(var);
177 }
178 });
179 }
180 }
181
182 ScopeBlockLoopInfo result;
183 } visitor;
184 visitor(scope_block->body);
185 return std::move(visitor.result);
186}

188/*!
189 * \brief Check whether the given sref_a is higher than or equal to sref_b.
190 */
191void CheckSRefHigherOrEqual(const StmtSRef& sref_a, const StmtSRef& sref_b) {
192 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref_b.get();
193 for (; p != nullptr; p = p->parent) {
194 if (p == sref_a.get()) {
195 return;
196 }
197 }
198 CHECK(false) << "Expect StmtSRef " << sref_a << "to be higher than or equal to " << sref_b;
199}

201/*!
202 * \brief Check the dominant property of a block:
203 * the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under the
204 * given root scope.
205 * \param self The schedule state.
206 * \param scope_root_sref The StmtSRef corresponding to the root scope.
207 * \param block_sref The block whose dominant property is to be checked.
208 * \return A boolean indicating if the block is a dominant block.
209 */
210bool IsDominantBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref,
211 const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
212 std::unordered_map<Buffer, Array<StmtSRef>, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> buffer_writers;
213 CheckSRefHigherOrEqual(scope_root_sref, block_sref);
214 const BlockNode* maybe_root_block = scope_root_sref->StmtAs<BlockNode>();
215 if (maybe_root_block) {
216 BlockScope scope = self->GetBlockScope(scope_root_sref);
217 buffer_writers = scope->buffer_writers;
218 } else {
219 // Collect all child blocks of root sub-tree, and merge their buffer writers.
220 Array<StmtSRef> child_block_srefs = GetChildBlockSRefOnSRefTree(self, scope_root_sref);
221 for (const StmtSRef& child_block_sref : child_block_srefs) {
222 BlockScope child_scope = self->GetBlockScope(child_block_sref);
223 for (const auto& it : child_scope->buffer_writers) {
224 buffer_writers.insert(it);
225 }
226 }
227 }
228 // Check whether the input block is the only writer of its outputs
229 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
230 for (const BufferRegion& write_region : block->writes) {
231 if (buffer_writers.count(write_region->buffer)) {
232 if (buffer_writers.at(write_region->buffer).size() != 1) {
233 return false;
234 }
235 }
236 }
237 return true;
238}

240/*!
241 * \brief A helper function that checks whether a given block is a complete block under the scope,
242 * or return the condition it violates if it is not a complete block
243 * \param self The schedule state
244 * \param block_sref The block to be checked
245 * \param scope_root_sref The sref to the root block of the scope that `block_sref` is in
246 * \return 0 if the block is a complete block, or a positive integer indicating which condition is
247 * first violated
248 */
249int CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
250 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
251 // Cond 1. All block vars are data parallel
252 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
253 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
254 if (iter_var->iter_type != kDataPar) {
255 return 1;
256 }
257 }
258 // Cond 2. Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output,
259 // dominating the reader of its output buffers
260 if (!IsDominantBlock(self, scope_root_sref, block_sref)) {
261 return 2;
262 }
263 // Cond 3. No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes
264 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> written_buffers;
265 written_buffers.reserve(block->writes.size());
266 for (const BufferRegion& write : block->writes) {
267 written_buffers.insert(write->buffer.get());
268 }
269 for (const BufferRegion& read : block->reads) {
270 if (written_buffers.count(read->buffer.get())) {
271 return 3;
272 }
273 }
274 return 0;
275}
276
277static const char* kCompleteBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a complete block:
2781) All block vars are data parallel
2792) Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers
2803) No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes)";
281
282static const char* kReductionBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a reduction block:
2831) The block has the `init` statement
2842) All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions
2853) All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars
2864) Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers
2875) The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers)";
288
289static const char* kLocalCompleteBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a local complete block:
2901) All block vars are data parallel
2912) Local Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under a given subtree
2923) No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes)";
293
294static const char* kLocalReductionBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a reduction block:
2951) The block has the `init` statement
2962) All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions
2973) All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars
2984) Local Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under a given subtree
2995) The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers)";
300
301bool IsCompleteBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
302 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
303 return CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref) == 0;
304}

306void CheckCompleteBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
307 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
308 class IncompleteBlockError : public ScheduleError {
309 public:
310 explicit IncompleteBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block, int violated_cond)
311 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)), violated_cond_(violated_cond) {}
312 String FastErrorString() const final { return "ScheduleError: Incomplete block"; }
313 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
314 std::ostringstream os;
315 os << "The block {0} is not a complete block - it violates condition #" << violated_cond_;
316 os << ".\n" << kCompleteBlockDefinition;
317 return os.str();
318 }
319 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
320 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
321 IRModule mod_;
322 Block block_;
323 int violated_cond_;
324 };
325
326 int error_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
327 if (error_code != 0) {
328 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
329 throw IncompleteBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), error_code);
330 }
331}

333/*!
334 * \brief A helper function that checks whether a given block is a reduction block under the scope,
335 * or return the condition it violates if it is not a reduction block
336 * \param self The schedule state
337 * \param block_sref The block to be checked
338 * \param scope_root_sref The sref to the root block of the scope that `block_sref` is in
339 * \return 0 if the block is a reduction block, or a positive integer indicating which condition is
340 * first violated
341 */
342int CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
343 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
344 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
345 // Cond 1. The block has the `init` statement.
346 if (!block->init.defined()) {
347 return 1;
348 }
349 // Cond 2. All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions.
350 if (!self->IsAffineBlockBinding(block_sref)) {
351 return 2;
352 }
353 // Cond 3. All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars. Meanwhile,
354 // we collect all the reduction block vars.
355 if (!ContainsOnlyDataParAndReductionBlockIter(block->iter_vars)) {
356 return 3;
357 }
358 // Cond 4. Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its
359 // output buffers.
360 if (!IsDominantBlock(self, scope_root_sref, block_sref)) {
361 return 4;
362 }
363 // Cond 5. The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers.
364 return ReductionIterNotIndexOutputBuffer(GetRef<Block>(block)) ? 0 : 5;
365}
366
367bool IsReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
368 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
369 return CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref) == 0;
370}
371
372void CheckReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
373 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
374 class NotReductionBlockError : public ScheduleError {
375 public:
376 explicit NotReductionBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block, int violated_cond)
377 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)), violated_cond_(violated_cond) {}
378 String FastErrorString() const final { return "ScheduleError: Not a reduction block"; }
379 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
380 std::ostringstream os;
381 os << "The block {0} is not a reduction block - it violates condition #" << violated_cond_;
382 os << ".\n" << kReductionBlockDefinition;
383 return os.str();
384 }
385 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
386 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
387 IRModule mod_;
388 Block block_;
389 int violated_cond_;
390 };
391
392 int error_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
393 if (error_code != 0) {
394 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
395 throw NotReductionBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), error_code);
396 }
397}

399void CheckCompleteOrReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
400 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
401 class NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError : public ScheduleError {
402 public:
403 explicit NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block,
404 int complete_block_error_code,
405 int reduction_block_error_code)
406 : mod_(mod),
407 block_(block),
408 complete_block_error_code_(complete_block_error_code),
409 reduction_block_error_code_(reduction_block_error_code) {}
410
411 String FastErrorString() const final {
412 return "ScheduleError: Not a complete or reduction block";
413 }
414 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
415 std::ostringstream os;
416 os << "The block {0} is not a complete block - it violates condition #"
417 << complete_block_error_code_;
418 os << ".\n" << kCompleteBlockDefinition;
419 os << "\nThe block is not a reduction block either - it violates condition #"
420 << reduction_block_error_code_;
421 os << ".\n" << kReductionBlockDefinition;
422 return os.str();
423 }
424 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
425 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
426
427 IRModule mod_;
428 Block block_;
429 int complete_block_error_code_;
430 int reduction_block_error_code_;
431 };
432
433 int complete_block_error_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
434 if (complete_block_error_code == 0) {
435 return;
436 }
437 int reduction_block_error_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
438 if (reduction_block_error_code == 0) {
439 return;
440 }
441 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
442 throw NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), complete_block_error_code,
443 reduction_block_error_code);
444}

446void CheckSubtreeCompactDataflow(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& subtree_root) {
447 class NotCompactDataFlowError : public ScheduleError {
448 public:
449 explicit NotCompactDataFlowError(IRModule mod, Stmt subtree_root, Block violate_block,
450 int local_complete_block_code, int local_reduction_block_code)
451 : mod_(std::move(mod)),
452 subtree_root_(std::move(subtree_root)),
453 violate_block_(std::move(violate_block)),
454 local_complete_block_code_(local_complete_block_code),
455 local_reduction_block_code_(local_reduction_block_code) {
456 ICHECK(subtree_root_->IsInstance<BlockNode>() || subtree_root_->IsInstance<ForNode>());
457 }
458 String FastErrorString() const final {
459 return "ScheduleError: The queried subtree root in SRef tree does not have compact dataflow, "
460 "because some of its child block on SRef tree is neither a local complete block nor a "
461 "local reduction block.";
462 }
463 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
464 std::ostringstream os;
465 os << "The queried subtree root {0} in SRef tree does not have compact dataflow, because "
466 "its child block {1} on SRef tree is neither a local complete block nor a local "
467 "reduction block.\n";
468 os << "It violates condition #" << local_complete_block_code_
469 << " as a local complete block.\n";
470 os << kLocalCompleteBlockDefinition << "\n";
471 os << "It violates condition #" << local_reduction_block_code_
472 << " as a local reduction block.\n";
473 os << kLocalReductionBlockDefinition << "\n";
474 return os.str();
475 }
476 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
477 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {subtree_root_, violate_block_}; }
478
479 IRModule mod_;
480 Stmt subtree_root_;
481 Block violate_block_;
482 int local_complete_block_code_;
483 int local_reduction_block_code_;
484 };
485
486 Array<StmtSRef> child_block_srefs = GetChildBlockSRefOnSRefTree(self, subtree_root);
487 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : child_block_srefs) {
488 int local_complete_block_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, subtree_root),
489 local_reduction_block_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, subtree_root);
490 if (local_complete_block_code != 0 && local_reduction_block_code != 0) {
491 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
492 throw NotCompactDataFlowError(self->mod, GetRef<Stmt>(subtree_root->stmt),
493 GetRef<Block>(block), local_complete_block_code,
494 local_reduction_block_code);
495 }
496 }
497}

499bool IsOutputBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
500 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
501 const BlockNode* scope_root = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_root_sref);
502 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
503 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> scope_allocated;
504 scope_allocated.reserve(scope_root->alloc_buffers.size());
505 for (const Buffer& buffer : scope_root->alloc_buffers) {
506 scope_allocated.insert(buffer.get());
507 }
508 for (const BufferRegion& buffer_region : block->writes) {
509 if (!scope_allocated.count(buffer_region->buffer.get())) {
510 return true;
511 }
512 }
513 return false;
514}

516void CheckNotOutputBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
517 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
518 class OutputBlockError : public ScheduleError {
519 public:
520 explicit OutputBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block) : mod_(mod), block_(block) {}
521 String FastErrorString() const final {
522 return "ScheduleError: Cannot operate on an output block";
523 }
524 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final { return "The block {0} is an output block"; }
525 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
526 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
527
528 IRModule mod_;
529 Block block_;
530 };
531 if (IsOutputBlock(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref)) {
532 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
533 throw OutputBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block));
534 }
535}

537std::vector<IterVarType> GetBlockVarTypes(const BlockNode* block) {
538 std::vector<IterVarType> results;
539 results.reserve(block->iter_vars.size());
540 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
541 results.push_back(iter_var->iter_type);
542 }
543 return results;
544}
545
546std::vector<IterVarType> GetBlockVarTypes(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
547 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
548 return GetBlockVarTypes(block);
549}
550
551bool IsWriteCache(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
552 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
553 if (block->writes.size() != 1) {
554 return false;
555 }
556 const BufferRegion& write_region = block->writes[0];
557 for (const BufferRegion& read_region : block->reads) {
558 auto [exists, surjective, injective, ordered, no_const_read, no_shift_read] =
559 AnalyzeReadWritePattern(read_region, write_region);
560 // https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=81767
561 (void)exists;
562 (void)surjective;
563 (void)no_const_read;
564 (void)no_shift_read;
565 if (!(injective && ordered)) {
566 return false;
567 }
568 }
569 return true;
570}

572/******** Binding ********/
573
574bool IsAffineBinding(const BlockRealize& realize, const Map<Var, Range>& loop_var_ranges,
575 arith::Analyzer* analyzer) {
576 if (loop_var_ranges.empty()) {
577 return true;
578 }
579 auto res = arith::DetectIterMap(
580 /*indices=*/realize->iter_values,
581 /*input_iters=*/loop_var_ranges,
582 /*predicate=*/realize->predicate,
583 /*check_level=*/arith::IterMapLevel::Surjective,
584 /*analyzer=*/analyzer);
585 if (res->indices.empty()) {
586 return false;
587 }
588 for (const arith::IterSumExpr& sum_expr : res->indices) {
589 const Array<arith::IterSplitExpr>& args = sum_expr->args;
590 if (!args.empty() && !is_one(args[0]->scale)) {
591 return false;
592 }
593 }
594 return true;
595}
596
597void CheckPartialAffineBinding(const ScheduleState& self, Block block,
598 const Optional<StmtSRef>& high_exclusive) {
599 class NotAffineBindingError : public ScheduleError {
600 public:
601 explicit NotAffineBindingError(IRModule mod, Block block, Optional<StmtSRef> high_exclusive)
602 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)) {
603 if (high_exclusive.defined()) {
604 high_exclusive_loop_ = high_exclusive.value()->StmtAs<ForNode>();
605 }
606 }
607 String FastErrorString() const final {
608 std::ostringstream ss;
609 if (high_exclusive_loop_) {
610 ss << "ScheduleError: The block is required to have an partial affine binding under "
611 << high_exclusive_loop_->loop_var;
612 } else {
613 ss << "ScheduleError: The block is required to have an affine binding";
614 }
615 return ss.str();
616 }
617 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
618 std::ostringstream ss;
619 if (high_exclusive_loop_) {
620 ss << "The block {0} is required to have an partial affine binding under "
621 << high_exclusive_loop_->loop_var;
622 } else {
623 ss << "The block {0} is required to have an affine binding";
624 }
625 return ss.str();
626 }
627 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
628 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
629 IRModule mod_;
630 Block block_;
631 const ForNode* high_exclusive_loop_{nullptr};
632 };
633
634 StmtSRef block_sref = self->stmt2ref.at(block.get());
635 if (self->IsAffineBlockBinding(block_sref)) {
636 // check block cached state for global affineness
637 return;
638 }
639 if (block_sref->parent && high_exclusive.defined()) {
640 // if it is not of global affine binding, check affineness under high_exclusive,
641 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
642 Map<Var, Range> dom_map =
643 LoopDomainOfSRefTreePath(GetRef<StmtSRef>(block_sref->parent), high_exclusive);
644 if (IsAffineBinding(GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref), dom_map, &analyzer)) {
645 return;
646 }
647 }
648 throw NotAffineBindingError(self->mod, std::move(block), high_exclusive);
649}
650
651void CheckAffineBinding(const ScheduleState& self, Block block) {
652 CheckPartialAffineBinding(self, std::move(block), NullOpt);
653}

683
684Map<Var, Range> LoopDomainOfSRefTreePath(const StmtSRef& low_inclusive,
685 const Optional<StmtSRef>& high_exclusive,
686 const runtime::StorageScope& extra_relax_scope) {
687 Map<Var, Range> result;
688 const StmtSRefNode* p = low_inclusive.get();
689 const StmtSRefNode* limit = static_cast<const StmtSRefNode*>(high_exclusive.get());
690 for (; p != limit; p = p->parent) {
691 const ForNode* loop = p->StmtAs<ForNode>();
692 if (loop == nullptr) {
693 break;
694 }
695 result.Set(loop->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(loop->min, loop->extent));
696 }
697 if (extra_relax_scope.rank != runtime::StorageRank::kGlobal) {
698 for (; p; p = p->parent) {
699 if (const ForNode* loop = p->StmtAs<ForNode>()) {
700 if (loop->kind == ForKind::kThreadBinding) {
701 const String& thread_tag = loop->thread_binding.value()->thread_tag;
702 if (CanRelaxStorageUnderThread(extra_relax_scope,
703 runtime::ThreadScope::Create(thread_tag))) {
704 result.Set(loop->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(loop->min, loop->extent));
705 }
706 }
707 }
708 }
709 }
710 return result;
711}
712
713Map<Var, PrimExpr> GetBindings(const BlockRealize& realize) {
714 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
715 const Array<IterVar>& all_lhs = block->iter_vars;
716 const Array<PrimExpr>& all_rhs = realize->iter_values;
717 ICHECK_EQ(all_lhs.size(), all_rhs.size());
718 Map<Var, PrimExpr> result;
719 for (int i = 0, n = all_lhs.size(); i < n; ++i) {
720 const IterVar& lhs = all_lhs[i];
721 const PrimExpr& rhs = all_rhs[i];
722 result.Set(lhs->var, rhs);
723 }
724 return result;
725}
726
727bool GetVarsTouchedByBlockIters(const BlockRealize& block_realize,
728 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* data_par_vars,
729 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* reduce_vars) {
730 Block block = block_realize->block;
731 ICHECK(block_realize->block.same_as(block))
732 << "ValueError: The input `block_realize` is required to be the exact BlockRealize of the "
733 "input block";
734
735 bool has_block_vars_of_other_types = false;
736 ICHECK_EQ(block->iter_vars.size(), block_realize->iter_values.size());
737 int n = static_cast<int>(block->iter_vars.size());
738 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
739 const IterVar& iter_var = block->iter_vars[i];
740 const PrimExpr& iter_value = block_realize->iter_values[i];
741 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* set = nullptr;
742 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
743 set = data_par_vars;
744 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kCommReduce) {
745 set = reduce_vars;
746 } else {
747 has_block_vars_of_other_types = true;
748 }
749 if (set == nullptr) {
750 continue;
751 }
752 Array<Var> vars_in_binding = UndefinedVars(iter_value);
753 for (const Var& var : vars_in_binding) {
754 set->insert(var.get());
755 }
756 }
757
758 return has_block_vars_of_other_types;
759}

807 Collector collector;
808 collector(stmt);
809 return std::move(collector.result_);
810 }
811
812 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* block_realize) final {
813 result_.push_back(GetRef<BlockRealize>(block_realize));

817 };

824 return Collector::Collect(block->body);
825 }
826 ICHECK(false) << "Unreachable";

866BlockRealize GetBlockRealize(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
867 struct BlockRealizeFinder : public StmtVisitor {
868 explicit BlockRealizeFinder(const BlockNode* target_block)
869 : target_block(target_block), result(nullptr) {}
870
871 void VisitStmt(const Stmt& stmt) final {
872 if (result != nullptr) {
873 return;
874 }
875 StmtVisitor::VisitStmt(stmt);
876 }
877
878 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* block_realize) final {
879 if (block_realize->block.get() == target_block) {
880 result = block_realize;
881 }
882 // No need to visit recursively, since the deeper BlockRealizes must not be the result.
883 }
884
885 const BlockNode* target_block;
886 const BlockRealizeNode* result;
887 };
888
889 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
890 if (block_sref->parent == nullptr) {
891 const PrimFuncNode* func = GetRootPrimFunc(self->mod, block, nullptr);
892 return Downcast<BlockRealize>(func->body);
893 } else {
894 BlockRealizeFinder finder(block);
895 finder(GetRef<Stmt>(block_sref->parent->stmt));
896 ICHECK(finder.result != nullptr)
897 << "InternalError: Cannot find the BlockRealize of block " << GetRef<Block>(block);
898 return GetRef<BlockRealize>(finder.result);
899 }

901
902IterVarType GetLoopIterType(const StmtSRef& loop_sref) {
903 const ForNode* loop = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loop_sref);
904 const Var& loop_var = loop->loop_var;
905 int n_spatial = 0;
906 int n_reduce = 0;
907 int n_other = 0;
908 auto f_visit = [&loop_var, &n_spatial, &n_reduce, &n_other](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
909 if (const auto* realize = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
910 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
911 // Number of block vars and their bindings
912 ICHECK_EQ(realize->iter_values.size(), block->iter_vars.size());
913 size_t n = realize->iter_values.size();
914 for (size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
915 const IterVar& iter_var = block->iter_vars[i];
916 const PrimExpr& binding = realize->iter_values[i];
917 // Categorize the current block var
918 int* ref = nullptr;
919 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
920 ref = &n_spatial;
921 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kCommReduce) {
922 ref = &n_reduce;
923 } else {
924 ref = &n_other;
925 }
926 // Visit the binding to see if `loop_var` appears
927 PostOrderVisit(binding, [&ref, &loop_var](const ObjectRef& obj) -> void {
928 if (obj.same_as(loop_var)) {
929 (*ref) += 1;
930 }
931 });
932 }
933 return false;
934 }
935 return true;
936 };
937 PreOrderVisit(loop->body, f_visit);
938 if (n_other) {
939 return IterVarType::kOpaque;
940 } else if (n_spatial && n_reduce) {
941 return IterVarType::kOpaque;
942 } else if (n_reduce) {
943 return IterVarType::kCommReduce;
944 } else {
945 return IterVarType::kDataPar;
946 }
947}
948
949StmtSRef GetSRefLowestCommonAncestor(const Array<StmtSRef>& srefs) {
950 CHECK(!srefs.empty()) << "ValueError: The input array is required to have at least one sref";
951
952 std::unordered_map<const StmtSRefNode*, size_t> sref_visited_cnt;
953 for (const StmtSRef& sref : srefs) {
954 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref.get();
955 while (p != nullptr) {
956 ++sref_visited_cnt[p];
957 p = p->parent;
958 }
959 }
960 size_t n_sref = srefs.size();
961 const StmtSRefNode* p = srefs[0].get();
962 while (p != nullptr && sref_visited_cnt[p] != n_sref) {
963 p = p->parent;
964 }
965 ICHECK(p != nullptr);
966 return GetRef<StmtSRef>(p);
967}

972
973std::pair<Array<StmtSRef>, std::vector<int>> CollectComputeLocation(const ScheduleState& self,
974 const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
975 Array<StmtSRef> location_srefs;
976 std::vector<int> location_indices;
977
978 // Step 1. Add the "compute-root" candidate. Add the "compute-inline" candidate if the block can
979 // be inlined.
980 if (CanComputeInline(self, block_sref)) {
981 location_srefs.push_back(StmtSRef::InlineMark());
982 location_indices.push_back(-2);
983 }
984 location_srefs.push_back(StmtSRef::RootMark());
985 location_indices.push_back(-1);
986
987 // Step 2. If the block has no consumer, there is no more candidate.
988 Array<StmtSRef> consumers = GetConsumers(self, block_sref);
989 if (consumers.empty()) {
990 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
991 }
992
993 // Step 3. Get the deepest loop that the input block can be computed at (namely "boundary"). If
994 // such a loop cannot be found, there is no more candidate and we just return.
995 StmtSRef loop_boundary = consumers.size() > 1 ? GetSRefLowestCommonAncestor(consumers)
996 : GetRef<StmtSRef>(consumers[0]->parent);
997 if (loop_boundary->StmtAs<ForNode>() == nullptr) {
998 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
999 }
1000
1001 // Step 4. Collect the loops outside the first consumer and locate the boundary loop. The position
1002 // of the boundary loop reveals the number of possible additional candidates.
1003 Array<StmtSRef> loop_srefs = GetLoops(consumers[0]);
1004 size_t lca_pos =
1005 std::find(loop_srefs.begin(), loop_srefs.end(), loop_boundary) - loop_srefs.begin();
1006 ICHECK_LT(lca_pos, loop_srefs.size());
1007 size_t n_candidate = lca_pos + 1;
1008
1009 // Step 5. Find the position of the deepest data-parallel loop among the candidate loops. This
1010 // position is used for removing the unwanted candidates from the perspective of performance.
1011 std::vector<IterVarType> loop_iter_types;
1012 loop_iter_types.reserve(n_candidate);
1013 int i_last_datapar = -1;
1014 for (size_t i = 0; i < n_candidate; ++i) {
1015 // TODO(siyuan): improve the performance
1016 IterVarType iter_type = GetLoopIterType(loop_srefs[i]);
1017 loop_iter_types.push_back(iter_type);
1018 if (iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1019 i_last_datapar = i;
1020 }
1021 }
1022 // Step 6. Check and add the candidates in turn according to the following rules:
1023 // - skip the unit loops (loops with extent 1);
1024 // - do not consider the data-parallel loops after a not-data-parallel loop;
1025 // - do not consider the trailing not-data-parallel loops.
1026 location_srefs.reserve(n_candidate + 2);
1027 location_indices.reserve(n_candidate + 2);
1028 bool visited_reduce = false;
1029 for (size_t i = 0; i < n_candidate; ++i) {
1030 const int64_t* loop_extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_srefs[i]);
1031 if (loop_extent != nullptr && *loop_extent == 1) {
1032 continue;
1033 }
1034
1035 if (loop_iter_types[i] == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1036 if (visited_reduce) {
1037 break;
1038 }
1039 } else {
1040 visited_reduce = true;
1041 if (static_cast<int>(i) > i_last_datapar) {
1042 break;
1043 }
1044 }
1045 if (CanComputeAt(self, block_sref, loop_srefs[i], true)) {
1046 location_srefs.push_back(loop_srefs[i]);
1047 location_indices.push_back(i);
1048 }
1049 }
1050
1051 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
1052}

1075
1076ProducerConsumerSplit ProducerConsumerSplit::Find(
1077 const ScheduleState& self, const Array<Stmt>& subtrees,
1078 const Array<StmtSRef>& producer_block_srefs, const Array<StmtSRef>& consumer_block_srefs,
1079 std::unordered_map<const BlockNode*, const BlockRealizeNode*>* block2realize) {
1080 class InsertionPointNotFoundError : public ScheduleError {
1081 public:
1082 explicit InsertionPointNotFoundError(IRModule mod, int last_producer_position,
1083 int first_consumer_position)
1084 : mod_(mod),
1085 last_producer_position_(last_producer_position),
1086 first_consumer_position_(first_consumer_position) {}
1087
1088 String FastErrorString() const final {
1089 return "ScheduleError: Cannot find the insertion point that satisfies the producer-consumer "
1090 "constraint";
1091 }
1092
1093 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
1094 return "Cannot find the insertion point that satisfies the producer-consumer constraint. In "
1095 "0-based indexing, the last producer appears in subtree " +
1096 std::to_string(last_producer_position_) +
1097 ", and the first consumer appears in subtree " +
1098 std::to_string(first_consumer_position_);
1099 }
1100
1101 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
1102
1103 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {}; }
1104
1105 private:
1106 IRModule mod_;
1107 int last_producer_position_;
1108 int first_consumer_position_;
1109 };
1110
1111 class Finder : public StmtVisitor {
1112 public:
1113 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* realize) final {
1114 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
1115 if (block2realize_) {
1116 block2realize_->emplace(block, realize);
1117 }
1118 if (producer_blocks_.count(block)) {
1119 ++this->n_producers_visited_;
1120 }
1121 if (consumer_blocks_.count(block)) {
1122 ++this->n_consumers_visited_;
1123 }
1124 }
1125
1126 std::unordered_map<const BlockNode*, const BlockRealizeNode*>* block2realize_;
1127 std::unordered_set<const StmtNode*> producer_blocks_;
1128 std::unordered_set<const StmtNode*> consumer_blocks_;
1129 int n_producers_visited_ = 0;
1130 int n_consumers_visited_ = 0;
1131 };
1132
1133 Finder finder;
1134 finder.block2realize_ = block2realize;
1135 // Set up the lookup table for producers
1136 finder.producer_blocks_.reserve(producer_block_srefs.size());
1137 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : producer_block_srefs) {
1138 finder.producer_blocks_.insert(block_sref->stmt);
1139 }
1140 // Set up the lookup table for consumers
1141 finder.consumer_blocks_.reserve(consumer_block_srefs.size());
1142 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : consumer_block_srefs) {
1143 finder.consumer_blocks_.insert(block_sref->stmt);
1144 }
1145 // Visit the subtrees
1146 int n = subtrees.size();
1147 int last_producer_position = -1;
1148 int first_consumer_position = n;
1149 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1150 int n_producers_visited_before = finder.n_producers_visited_;
1151 int n_consumers_visited_before = finder.n_consumers_visited_;
1152 finder(subtrees[i]);
1153 // Check if the subtree contains at least a producer
1154 if (finder.n_producers_visited_ != n_producers_visited_before) {
1155 last_producer_position = i;
1156 }
1157 // Check if the subtree contains at least a consumer
1158 if (finder.n_consumers_visited_ != n_consumers_visited_before) {
1159 if (first_consumer_position == n) {
1160 first_consumer_position = i;
1161 }
1162 }
1163 }
1164 if (last_producer_position >= first_consumer_position) {
1165 throw InsertionPointNotFoundError(self->mod, last_producer_position, first_consumer_position);
1166 }
1167 return ProducerConsumerSplit{last_producer_position, //
1168 first_consumer_position, //
1169 finder.n_producers_visited_, //
1170 finder.n_consumers_visited_};
1171}

1173/******** Block-buffer relation ********/
1174
1175BufferRegion GetNthAccessBufferRegion(const ScheduleState& self, const Block& block, int n,
1176 BufferIndexType index_type) {
1177 class BufferIndexOutOfRangeError : public ScheduleError {
1178 public:
1179 explicit BufferIndexOutOfRangeError(IRModule mod, Block block, int buffer_index,
1180 BufferIndexType index_type)
1181 : mod_(std::move(mod)),
1182 block_(std::move(block)),
1183 buffer_index_(buffer_index),
1184 index_type_(index_type) {}
1185
1186 String FastErrorString() const final {
1187 if (index_type_ == BufferIndexType::kWrite) {
1188 return "ScheduleError: The input `buffer_index` is out of range. It is required to be in "
1189 "range "
1190 "[0, num_write_regions) where `num_write_regions` is the number of buffer regions "
1191 "written by the block.";
1192 } else {
1193 return "ScheduleError: The input `buffer_index` is out of range. It is required to be in "
1194 "range "
1195 "[0, num_read_regions) where `num_read_regions` is the number of buffer regions "
1196 "read by the block.";
1197 }
1198 }
1199
1200 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
1201 std::ostringstream os;
1202 size_t num =
1203 index_type_ == BufferIndexType::kWrite ? block_->writes.size() : block_->reads.size();
1204 os << "The block {0} has " << num << " " << BufferIndexType2Str(index_type_)
1205 << " regions, so `buffer_index` is required to be in [0, " << num
1206 << "). However, the input `buffer_index` is " << buffer_index_
1207 << ", which is out of the expected range.";
1208 return os.str();
1209 }
1210
1211 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
1212 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
1213
1214 private:
1215 IRModule mod_;
1216 Block block_;
1217 int buffer_index_;
1218 BufferIndexType index_type_;
1219 };
1220
1221 const Array<BufferRegion>& access_region =
1222 index_type == BufferIndexType::kWrite ? block->writes : block->reads;
1223
1224 if (n < 0 || static_cast<int>(access_region.size()) <= n) {
1225 throw BufferIndexOutOfRangeError(self->mod, block, n, index_type);
1226 }
1227 return access_region[n];
1228}
1229
1230Buffer GetNthAccessBuffer(const ScheduleState& self, const Block& block, int n,
1231 BufferIndexType index_type) {
1232 return GetNthAccessBufferRegion(self, block, n, index_type)->buffer;
1233}
1234
1235std::pair<Optional<StmtSRef>, bool> GetBufferDefiningSite(const StmtSRef& block_sref,
1236 const Buffer& buffer) {
1237 // Climb up along the sref tree, and find the block where `buffer` is in alloc_buffers or
1238 // match_buffers.
1239 const StmtSRefNode* defining_site_sref = block_sref.get();
1240 while (defining_site_sref != nullptr) {
1241 const auto* block = defining_site_sref->StmtAs<BlockNode>();
1242 // If this sref is not a block sref, skip it.
1243 if (block == nullptr) {
1244 defining_site_sref = defining_site_sref->parent;
1245 continue;
1246 }
1247 // Try to find the buffer in `allloc_buffers`
1248 for (const Buffer& alloc_buffer : block->alloc_buffers) {
1249 if (buffer.same_as(alloc_buffer)) {
1250 return {GetRef<StmtSRef>(defining_site_sref), true};
1251 }
1252 }
1253 // We do not allow the buffer being defined in `match_buffer`.
1254 for (const MatchBufferRegion match_buffer : block->match_buffers) {
1255 if (buffer.same_as(match_buffer)) {
1256 return {GetRef<StmtSRef>(defining_site_sref), false};
1257 }
1258 }
1259 defining_site_sref = defining_site_sref->parent;
1260 }
1261 // If we cannot find the defining site block, it means that the buffer must be in the function's
1262 // buffer_map, which isn't an intermediate buffer.
1263 return {NullOpt, false};
1264}

1268StmtSRef GetSRefTreeRoot(const StmtSRef& sref) {
1269 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref.get();
1270 for (; p->parent != nullptr; p = p->parent) {
1271 }
1272 return GetRef<StmtSRef>(p);
1273}

1277bool HasOp(const Stmt& stmt, const Array<Op>& ops) {
1278 std::unordered_set<const Object*> op_set;
1279 op_set.reserve(ops.size());
1280 for (const Op& op : ops) {
1281 op_set.insert(op.operator->());
1282 }
1283 bool found = false;
1284 PreOrderVisit(stmt, [&found, &op_set](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1285 if (found) {
1286 return false;
1287 }
1288 if (const auto* call = obj.as<CallNode>()) {
1289 if (op_set.count(call->op.operator->())) {
1290 found = true;
1291 }
1292 }
1293 return !found;
1294 });
1295 return found;
1296}
1297
1298bool HasIfThenElse(const Stmt& stmt) {
1299 bool has_branch = false;
1300 auto f_visit = [&has_branch](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1301 if (has_branch) {
1302 // stop visiting
1303 return false;
1304 }
1305 if (const auto* realize = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
1306 // Case 1: BlockRealize
1307 if (!is_one(realize->predicate)) {
1308 has_branch = true;
1309 }
1310 } else if (obj->IsInstance<IfThenElseNode>() || obj->IsInstance<SelectNode>()) {
1311 // Case 2: IfThenElse / Select
1312 has_branch = true;
1313 } else if (const auto* call = obj.as<CallNode>()) {
1314 // Case 3: Call the `if_then_else` operator
1315 static const Op& op_if_then_else = Op::Get("tir.if_then_else");
1316 if (call->op.same_as(op_if_then_else)) {
1317 has_branch = true;
1318 }
1319 }
1320 return !has_branch;
1321 };
1322 PreOrderVisit(stmt, f_visit);
1323 return has_branch;
1324}
1325
1326std::tuple</*exists=*/bool,
1327 /*surjective=*/bool,
1328 /*injective=*/bool,
1329 /*ordered=*/bool,
1330 /*no_const_read=*/bool,
1331 /*no_shift_read=*/bool>
1332AnalyzeReadWritePattern(const BufferRegion& read_region, const BufferRegion& write_region) {
1333 static constexpr const std::tuple<bool, bool, bool, bool, bool, bool> kNotExist =
1334 std::make_tuple(false, false, false, false, false, false);
1335 // Step 1. Extract the write indices
1336 int w_dim = write_region->buffer->shape.size();
1337 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, int> var2idx;
1338 var2idx.reserve(w_dim);
1339 for (int i = 0; i < w_dim; ++i) {
1340 const Range& dom = write_region->region[i];
1341 if (as_const_int(dom->extent) == nullptr) {
1342 return kNotExist;
1343 }
1344 if (const auto* v = dom->min.as<VarNode>()) {
1345 var2idx.emplace(v, i);
1346 } else {
1347 return kNotExist;
1348 }
1349 }
1350 // Step 2. Map each read index to a write index
1351 bool no_const_read = true;
1352 bool no_shift_read = true;
1353 int r_dim = read_region->buffer->shape.size();
1354 std::vector<int> mapped(r_dim, -1);
1355 for (int i = 0; i < r_dim; ++i) {
1356 const Range& dom = read_region->region[i];
1357 if (as_const_int(dom->extent) == nullptr) {
1358 return kNotExist;
1359 }
1360 // Case 1. Read index is a constant
1361 if (as_const_int(dom->min) != nullptr) {
1362 no_const_read = false;
1363 continue;
1364 }
1365 // Case 2. Read index cannot be recognized as `var +/- const`
1366 // where `var` is a write index and `const` is an optional constant shift
1367 Optional<IntImm> opt_const = NullOpt;
1368 const VarNode* var =
1369 static_cast<const VarNode*>(AnalyzeVarWithShift(dom->min, &opt_const).get());
1370 if (var == nullptr || !var2idx.count(var)) {
1371 return kNotExist;
1372 }
1373 // Case 3. Read index is `var +/- const`
1374 mapped[i] = var2idx.at(var);
1375 if (opt_const.defined()) {
1376 no_shift_read = false;
1377 }
1378 }
1379 // Step 3. Check if the mapping is ordered, and count how many times each var is mapped
1380 std::vector<int> mapped_counter(w_dim, 0);
1381 bool ordered = true;
1382 int last_mapped = -1;
1383 for (int i : mapped) {
1384 if (i != -1) {
1385 ++mapped_counter[i];
1386 if (last_mapped != -1 && last_mapped > i) {
1387 ordered = false;
1388 }
1389 last_mapped = i;
1390 }
1391 }
1392 // Step 4. Check if the mapping is surjective or injective
1393 // Surjective: each write index is mapped at least once
1394 // Injective: each write index is mapped at most once
1395 bool surjective = true;
1396 bool injective = true;
1397 for (int cnt : mapped_counter) {
1398 if (cnt == 0) {
1399 surjective = false;
1400 } else if (cnt >= 2) {
1401 injective = false;
1402 }
1403 }
1404 return std::make_tuple(/*exist=*/true, surjective, injective, ordered, no_const_read,
1405 no_shift_read);
1406}

1411 class InvalidStorageScopeError : public ScheduleError {

1414 : mod_(std::move(mod)), storage_scope_(std::move(storage_scope)) {}
1415

1418 }
1419

1421 return "The input storage scope \"" + storage_scope_ + "\" is invalid.";
1422 }
1423
1424 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {}; }
1425 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
1426
1427 private:
1428 IRModule mod_;
1429 String storage_scope_;
1430 };
1431
1432 try {

1434 } catch (...) {

1439bool IsSpatial(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1440 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1441 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1442 if (iter_var->iter_type != IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1443 return false;
1444 }
1445 }
1446 return true;
1447}
1448
1449bool IsTrivialBinding(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1450 TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1451 Array<StmtSRef> loops = GetLoops(block_sref);
1452 Array<PrimExpr> binds = GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref)->iter_values;
1453 if (loops.size() != binds.size()) {
1454 return false;
1455 }
1456 for (int i = 0, n = loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1457 const ForNode* loop = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i]);
1458 if (binds[i].get() != loop->loop_var.get()) {
1459 return false;
1460 }
1461 }
1462 return true;
1463}
1464
1465bool NeedsMultiLevelTiling(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1466 if (HasBeenMultiLevelTiled(block_sref)) {
1467 return false;
1468 }
1469 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1470 if (block->writes.size() != 1 || block->reads.empty() || IsSpatial(block_sref) ||
1471 !IsTrivialBinding(self, block_sref)) {
1472 return false;
1473 }
1474 const BufferNode* write_buffer = block->writes[0]->buffer.get();
1475 // Step 1. Sort out spatial block variables. Skip the block iters of domain [0, 1), since such
1476 // block iters distracts the following check of the unused block iters.
1477 std::vector<const VarNode*> spatial_block_vars;
1478 spatial_block_vars.reserve(block->iter_vars.size());
1479 for (const IterVar& block_var : block->iter_vars) {
1480 const int64_t* dom_min = as_const_int(block_var->dom->min);
1481 const int64_t* dom_extent = as_const_int(block_var->dom->extent);
1482 bool has_trivial_dom =
1483 dom_min != nullptr && dom_extent != nullptr && *dom_min == 0 && *dom_extent == 1;
1484 if (block_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar && !has_trivial_dom) {
1485 spatial_block_vars.push_back(block_var->var.get());
1486 }
1487 }
1488 // Step 2. Enumerate each read region, check the number of block vars that are not used
1489 // to index the read region
1490 int total_unused_block_vars = 0;
1491 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> read_buffers;
1492 read_buffers.reserve(block->reads.size());
1493 for (const BufferRegion& buffer_region : block->reads) {
1494 const BufferNode* buffer = buffer_region->buffer.get();
1495 const Array<Range>& regions = buffer_region->region;
1496 // Step 2.1. Duplication of read buffers are not allowed
1497 if (read_buffers.insert(buffer).second == false) {
1498 return false;
1499 }
1500 // Step 2.2. Skip the reduction buffer
1501 if (buffer == write_buffer) {
1502 continue;
1503 }
1504 // Step 2.3. Collect the block vars that are used to index the read region
1505 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> vars;
1506 for (const Range& range : regions) {
1507 if (as_const_int(range->extent) == nullptr) {
1508 return false;
1509 }
1510 for (const Var& var : UndefinedVars(range->min)) {
1511 vars.insert(var.get());
1512 }
1513 }
1514 // Step 2.4. Check if the block vars are not used to index the read region
1515 int n_unused_block_vars = 0;
1516 for (const VarNode* block_var : spatial_block_vars) {
1517 if (vars.count(block_var) == 0) {
1518 ++n_unused_block_vars;
1519 }
1520 }
1521 total_unused_block_vars += n_unused_block_vars;
1522 }
1523 return total_unused_block_vars >= 1;
1524}

1526bool IsSpatialPrimFunc(const PrimFunc& func) {
1527 bool result = true;
1528 PreOrderVisit(func->body, [&result](const ObjectRef& obj) {
1529 if (result == false) {
1530 return false;
1531 }
1532 if (const auto* block = obj.as<BlockNode>()) {
1533 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1534 if (iter_var->iter_type != IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1535 result = false;
1536 return false;
1537 }
1538 }
1539 }
1540 return true;
1541 });
1542 return result;
1543}
1544
1545std::pair<int64_t, int64_t> GetCumulativeSpaceAndReductionLength(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
1546 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1547 Array<tir::StmtSRef> loops = tir::GetLoops(block_sref);
1548 int64_t cum_space_len = 1, cum_reduce_len = 1;
1549 /*
1550 * Return (-1, -1) if
1551 * 1. there is some loop with type other than kDataPar and kCommReduce;
1552 * 2. there is some loop which is dynamic.
1553 */
1554 for (const tir::StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
1555 tir::IterVarType type = GetLoopIterType(loop_sref);
1556 if (type == tir::kDataPar) {
1557 const int64_t* extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_sref);
1558 if (*extent != -1) {
1559 cum_space_len *= *extent;
1560 } else {
1561 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
1562 }
1563 } else if (type == tir::kCommReduce) {
1564 const int64_t* extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_sref);
1565 if (*extent != -1) {
1566 cum_reduce_len *= *extent;
1567 } else {
1568 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
1569 }
1570 } else {
1571 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
1572 }
1573 }
1574 return std::make_pair(cum_space_len, cum_reduce_len);
1575}
1576
1577bool NeedsRFactorOrCrossThreadReduction(const tir::ScheduleState& self, //
1578 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref, //
1579 int64_t max_parallel_extent, //
1580 int64_t max_parallel_basic) {
1581 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1582 Array<tir::StmtSRef> loops = tir::GetLoops(block_sref);
1583
1584 // Cond 1. The block must have at lease one write buffer
1585 if (block->writes.size() == 0) {
1586 return false;
1587 }
1588
1589 // Cond 2. The block is a reduction block and has trivial binding.
1590 const StmtSRef& scope_sref = GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref,
1591 /*require_stage_pipeline=*/false);
1592 if (!IsReductionBlock(self, block_sref, scope_sref) //
1593 || !IsTrivialBinding(self, block_sref) //
1594 || HasBeenMultiLevelTiled(block_sref)) {
1595 return false;
1596 }
1597
1598 // Cond 3. Every the loop axis must be either spatial axis or reduction axis.
1599 for (const tir::StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
1600 const tir::IterVarType& type = GetLoopIterType(loop_sref);
1601 if (type != tir::kDataPar && type != tir::kCommReduce) {
1602 return false;
1603 }
1604 }
1605
1606 // Cond 4. Whether there is at least one reduction loop.
1607 // Cond 5. The loops are continuous, and the body of the innermost loop is exactly the block.
1608 bool has_reduction_loop = false;
1609 for (size_t i = 0; i < loops.size(); ++i) {
1610 // Cond 4.
1611 if (GetLoopIterType(loops[i]) == tir::kCommReduce) {
1612 has_reduction_loop = true;
1613 }
1614
1615 // Cond 5.
1616 const ForNode* loop_i = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i]);
1617 if (i < loops.size() - 1) {
1618 const ForNode* loop_i1 = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i + 1]);
1619 if (loop_i->body.get() != loop_i1) {
1620 return false;
1621 }
1622 } else {
1623 const auto* block_realize = loop_i->body.as<tir::BlockRealizeNode>();
1624 if (!block_realize || block_realize->block.get() != block) {
1625 return false;
1626 }
1627 }
1628 }
1629 if (!has_reduction_loop) {
1630 return false;
1631 }
1632
1633 // Cond 6. Can successfully calculating the cumulative loop length.
1634 auto [cum_space_len, cum_reduce_len] = GetCumulativeSpaceAndReductionLength(self, block_sref);
1635 if (cum_space_len == -1 || cum_reduce_len == -1) {
1636 return false;
1637 }
1638
1639 // Cond 7.
1640 if (NeedsMultiLevelTiling(self, block_sref)) {
1641 // Do not use rfactor/cross-thread-reduction if we have enough parallelism on spatial loops.
1642 return !(cum_space_len >= cum_reduce_len || cum_space_len > max_parallel_extent);
1643 } else {
1644 // Always try rfactor/cross-thread-reduction for other reduction blocks.
1645 return cum_reduce_len > 1;
1646 }
1647}

1649TVM_REGISTER_NODE_TYPE(TensorizeInfoNode);
1650
1651/*! \brief Auxiliary data structure of information extracted from tensor intrin description */
1652struct TensorIntrinDescInfo {
1653 /*! \brief The block of the description function, which is the (unique) direct child of the root
1654 * block.
1655 */
1656 const BlockRealizeNode* desc_block = nullptr;
1657 /*! \brief The loops of the description function, in the order from outer loops to inner ones. */
1658 std::vector<const tir::ForNode*> desc_loops;
1659 /*! \brief The loop variables. */
1660 std::unordered_set<const tir::VarNode*> desc_loop_vars;
1661};
1662
1663/*!
1664 * \brief Extract auxilary information from the tensor intrin description.
1665 * \param analyze The arithmetic analyzer
1666 * \param desc_func The description PrimFunc
1667 * \return The auxilary information
1668 */
1669TensorIntrinDescInfo ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(arith::Analyzer* analyzer,
1670 const PrimFunc& desc_func) {
1671 TensorIntrinDescInfo info;
1672 const auto* desc_scope_realize = desc_func->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>();
1673 ICHECK(desc_scope_realize);
1674 {
1675 auto f_visit = [&](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1676 // Extract the block
1677 if (const auto* block = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
1678 info.desc_block = block;
1679 return false;
1680 }
1681 // Extract the loops
1682 if (const auto* loop = obj.as<ForNode>()) {
1683 info.desc_loops.push_back(loop);
1684 info.desc_loop_vars.insert(loop->loop_var.get());
1685 if (!analyzer->CanProve(loop->min == 0)) {
1686 return false;
1687 }
1688 }
1689 return true;
1690 };
1691 tir::PostOrderVisit(desc_scope_realize->block->body, f_visit);
1692 std::reverse(info.desc_loops.begin(), info.desc_loops.end());
1693 ICHECK(info.desc_block);
1694 }
1695 return info;
1696}
1697
1698Optional<TensorizeInfo> GetTensorizeLoopMapping(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
1699 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
1700 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func,
1701 bool allow_padding) {
1702 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
1703 const tir::BlockRealize& block = tir::GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref);
1704 // Step 1. Analyze desc_func, extract its block, loops and loop vars
1705 TensorIntrinDescInfo desc_info = ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(&analyzer, desc_func);
1706 // Step 2. Collect loops from block_sref
1707 const tir::StmtSRef& scope_sref = GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref, false);
1708 TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_sref);
1709 std::vector<const tir::ForNode*> block_loops;
1710 std::unordered_set<const tir::VarNode*> block_loop_vars;
1711 {
1712 for (const tir::StmtSRefNode* loop_sref = block_sref->parent;; loop_sref = loop_sref->parent) {
1713 const auto* loop = loop_sref->StmtAs<tir::ForNode>();
1714 if (loop == nullptr || loop->body->IsInstance<tir::SeqStmtNode>()) {
1715 break;
1716 }
1717 block_loops.push_back(loop);
1718 block_loop_vars.insert(loop->loop_var.get());
1719 if (!analyzer.CanProve(loop->min == 0)) {
1720 return NullOpt;
1721 }
1722 }
1723 std::reverse(block_loops.begin(), block_loops.end());
1724 }
1725 // Step 3. Map from block loops to desc block loops
1726 const std::vector<const ForNode*>& desc_loops = desc_info.desc_loops;
1727 const std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>& desc_loop_vars = desc_info.desc_loop_vars;
1728 const BlockRealizeNode* desc_block = desc_info.desc_block;
1729 ObjectPtr<TensorizeInfoNode> ret = make_object<TensorizeInfoNode>();
1730 const int n_block_vars = block->iter_values.size();
1731 const int n_desc_vars = desc_block->iter_values.size();
1732 const int offset = n_block_vars - n_desc_vars;
1733
1734 std::unordered_map<int, int> block_index_to_padding; // padding of each block iter if necessary
1735
1736 if (offset < 0) {
1737 return NullOpt;
1738 }
1739
1740 const std::vector<IterVarType> iter_types_block = GetBlockVarTypes(block_sref);
1741 const std::vector<IterVarType> iter_types_desc = GetBlockVarTypes(desc_block->block.get());
1742
1743 ICHECK(desc_loops.size() == static_cast<size_t>(n_desc_vars));
1744 ICHECK(block_loops.size() == iter_types_block.size());
1745
1746 // We assume that the orders of iter_vars in the target and the desc block are consistent.
1747 // Based on that assumption, the following logic supports arbitrary permutations of a loop order,
1748 // such as
1749
1750 // for k:
1751 // for i:
1752 // for j:
1753 // C[i, j] += A[i, k] * B[k, j]
1754
1755 // or
1756
1757 // for i:
1758 // for j:
1759 // for k:
1760 // C[i, j] += A[i, k] * B[k, j]
1761
1762 int next_block_ind = block_loops.size() - 1;
1763 for (int i_desc = n_desc_vars - 1; i_desc >= 0; --i_desc) {
1764 // Step 3.1. Find the corresponding loop of the i_desc-th block var of desc
1765 const PrimExpr& desc_bind = desc_block->iter_values[i_desc];
1766 const tir::ForNode* desc_loop = nullptr;
1767 IterVarType iter_type_desc = iter_types_desc[i_desc];
1768 for (int i = 0, n = desc_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1769 // Check if desc_bind = loops[i]->loop_var + stuff-irrelevant-of-loop-vars
1770 PrimExpr residual = analyzer.Simplify(desc_bind - desc_loops[i]->loop_var);
1771 if (!UsesVar(residual,
1772 [&desc_loop_vars](const VarNode* var) { return desc_loop_vars.count(var); })) {
1773 desc_loop = desc_loops[i];
1774 iter_type_desc = iter_types_desc[i];
1775 break;
1776 }
1777 }
1778 if (desc_loop == nullptr || desc_loop->extent.as<IntImmNode>() == nullptr) {
1779 return NullOpt;
1780 }
1781
1782 const IntImmNode* int_desc_extent = desc_loop->extent.as<IntImmNode>();
1783
1784 // Step 3.2. Find the corresponding iter_value of the target block with a matching iterator type
1785 PrimExpr block_bind;
1786 int current_block_ind = next_block_ind;
1787 for (; current_block_ind >= 0; --current_block_ind) {
1788 if (iter_types_block[current_block_ind] == iter_type_desc) {
1789 next_block_ind = current_block_ind - 1;
1790 block_bind = block->iter_values[current_block_ind];
1791 break;
1792 }
1793 }
1794
1795 if (!block_bind.defined()) return NullOpt;
1796
1797 // Step 3.3. Find the corresponding loop of the target block
1798 for (int i = 0, n = block_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1799 // Check if block_bind = block_loops[i]->loop_var + stuff-irrelevant-of-loop-vars
1800 const tir::ForNode* block_loop = block_loops[i];
1801 const tir::StmtSRef& block_loop_sref = self->stmt2ref[block_loop];
1802 // Skip i-th loop if it has already been mapped
1803 if (ret->loop_map.find(block_loop_sref) != ret->loop_map.end()) continue;
1804
1805 PrimExpr residual = analyzer.Simplify(block_bind - block_loops[i]->loop_var);
1806 if (UsesVar(residual,
1807 [&block_loop_vars](const VarNode* var) { return block_loop_vars.count(var); })) {
1808 continue;
1809 }
1810 // padding is allowed only when the block has trivial bindings
1811 if (allow_padding && !is_zero(residual)) {
1812 allow_padding = false;
1813 }
1814
1815 const IntImmNode* int_block_extent = block_loops[i]->extent.as<IntImmNode>();
1816
1817 // Check divisibility
1818 if (!int_block_extent) {
1819 return NullOpt;
1820 }
1821 int64_t remainder = int_block_extent->value % int_desc_extent->value;
1822 if (remainder != 0) {
1823 if (allow_padding) {
1824 // If the block loop is not divisible by the desc loop, we pad the block loop to make it
1825 // divisible if padding is allowed.
1826 block_index_to_padding[current_block_ind] = int_desc_extent->value - remainder;
1827 } else {
1828 return NullOpt;
1829 }
1830 }
1831
1832 ret->loop_map.Set(block_loop_sref, GetRef<tir::For>(desc_loop));
1833 break;
1834 }
1835 }
1836
1837 for (int i = 0, n = desc_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1838 ret->desc_loop_indexer.Set(GetRef<tir::For>(desc_loops[i]), Integer(i));
1839 }
1840 if (!block_index_to_padding.empty()) {
1841 if (!allow_padding) {
1842 return NullOpt;
1843 }
1844 Array<Integer> paddings;
1845 for (int i = 0, n = block->block->iter_vars.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1846 const IterVar& iter_var = block->block->iter_vars[i];
1847 if (auto it = block_index_to_padding.find(i); it != block_index_to_padding.end()) {
1848 paddings.push_back(IntImm(iter_var->var.dtype(), it->second));
1849 } else {
1850 paddings.push_back(IntImm(iter_var->var.dtype(), 0));
1851 }
1852 }
1853 ret->block_iter_paddings = std::move(paddings);
1854 }
1855
1856 return TensorizeInfo(ret);
1857}
1858
1859TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("tir.schedule.IsSpatialPrimFunc").set_body_typed(IsSpatialPrimFunc);
1860TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("tir.schedule.GetTensorizeLoopMapping")
1861 .set_body_typed([](Schedule sch, BlockRV block, PrimFunc desc_func, bool allow_padding) {
1862 return GetTensorizeLoopMapping(sch->state(), sch->GetSRef(block), desc_func, allow_padding);
1863 });

1865/******** Auto Tensorization ********/
1866
1867/*! \brief IndexMap proposer for layout transformation in auto tensorization. */
1868class AutoTensorizeMappingProposer {
1869 public:
1870 static Array<IndexMap> ProposeMappings(const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor,
1871 arith::Analyzer* analyzer) {
1872 AutoTensorizeMappingProposer proposer(extractor, analyzer);
1873 proposer.CollectFeasibleSet();
1874 return proposer.ProposeAllFuseMapping();
1875 }
1876
1877 private:
1878 explicit AutoTensorizeMappingProposer(const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor,
1879 arith::Analyzer* analyzer)
1880 : extractor_(extractor), analyzer_(analyzer) {}
1881
1882 using VarSet = std::unordered_set<Var, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual>;
1883
1884 void CollectFeasibleSet() {
1885 // Collect the set of potential iter var mapping between the workload and the tensor intrin.
1886 // We analyze the appearance of each variable in the buffer indices of each buffer on LHS and
1887 // RHS. The appearance of a variable in the buffer indices is encoded as bit-masks (BufferMask).
1888 // Variables on the LHS and the RHS with the same bit-mask and the same iter type are potential
1889 // mappings.
1890 //
1891 // For example, consider the conv2d case. We will try to match the workload
1892 // conv2d[n, h, w, c] = sum_{rh, rw, rc} X[n, h + rh, w + rw, c + rc] * W[rh, rw, rc, c]
1893 // against a matmul tensor intrin
1894 // C[m, n] = sum_{k} A[m, k] * B[k, n]
1895 // First we extract the correspondence of the buffers: conv2d <=> C, A <=> X, B <=> W.
1896 // Then for each variable, we extract the buffers where it is used for indexing.
1897 // Take the variable m on the RHS as an example. m is used to index buffer A and C. On the LHS,
1898 // we will find the variables used to index only the exact corresponding buffers conv2d and X
1899 // (the variable is not allowed to index other buffers). In this case, n, h, w is used to index
1900 // both buffer conv2d and W, and not in other buffers. Therefore, {n, h, w} <=> m is a potential
1901 // mapping.
1902
1903 // Note: the mapping is not unique when multiple variables on RHS has the same bit-mask.
1904 // This is currently not supported.
1905
1906 using BufferMask = std::vector<bool>;
1907
1908 // Step 1: Assign an index to each buffer in LHS and RHS
1909 std::unordered_map<Buffer, int, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectEqual> rhs_buffer_index;
1910 std::unordered_map<Buffer, int, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectEqual> lhs_buffer_index;
1911 {
1912 int i = 0;
1913 for (const auto& kv : extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_) {
1914 const Buffer& rhs_buffer = kv.first;
1915 const Buffer& lhs_buffer = kv.second;
1916 rhs_buffer_index[rhs_buffer] = i;
1917 lhs_buffer_index[lhs_buffer] = i;
1918 ++i;
1919 }
1920 }
1921
1922 // Step 2: Compute the buffer mask
1923 ICHECK_EQ(rhs_buffer_index.size(), lhs_buffer_index.size());
1924 int num_buffers = rhs_buffer_index.size();
1925 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, std::vector<bool>> rhs_buffer_masks, lhs_buffer_masks;
1926 // helper function to initialize or update the buffer mask
1927 auto update_mask = [&](const VarNode* var,
1928 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, std::vector<bool>>* masks, int i) {
1929 if (!masks->count(var)) {
1930 (*masks)[var].resize(num_buffers);
1931 }
1932 (*masks)[var][i] = true;
1933 };
1934
1935 for (const auto& it : extractor_->rhs_buffer_indices_map_) {
1936 const Buffer& rhs_buffer = it.first;
1937 for (const PrimExpr& rhs_index : it.second) {
1938 if (const VarNode* var_node = rhs_index.as<VarNode>()) {
1939 update_mask(var_node, &rhs_buffer_masks, rhs_buffer_index.at(rhs_buffer));
1940 } else {
1941 LOG(FATAL) << "ValueError: Buffer index " << rhs_index
1942 << " other that variables in tensor intrinsics is not supported.";
1943 }
1944 }
1945
1946 auto lhs_buffer_it = extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_.find(rhs_buffer);
1947 ICHECK(lhs_buffer_it != extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_.end());
1948 const Buffer& lhs_buffer = lhs_buffer_it->second;
1949 for (const PrimExpr& index : extractor_->lhs_buffer_indices_map_.at(lhs_buffer)) {
1950 PreOrderVisit(index, [&](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1951 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
1952 update_mask(var, &lhs_buffer_masks, lhs_buffer_index.at(lhs_buffer));
1953 }
1954 return true;
1955 });
1956 }
1957 }
1958
1959 // Step 3: Find variables on LHS and RHS with the same buffer mask. Ensure LHS and RHS vars
1960 // have the same iter type.
1961 std::unordered_map<BufferMask, VarSet> mask_to_rhs_vars;
1962 for (const auto& kv : rhs_buffer_masks) {
1963 const VarNode* rhs_var = kv.first;
1964 const BufferMask& mask = kv.second;
1965 mask_to_rhs_vars[mask].insert(GetRef<Var>(rhs_var));
1966 }
1967 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, IterVarType> rhs_var_iter_type;
1968 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
1969 rhs_var_iter_type.emplace(iter->var.get(), iter->iter_type);
1970 }
1971 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->lhs_iters_) {
1972 auto& potential_mappings = lhs_feasible_vars_[iter->var];
1973 VarSet rhs_candidates = mask_to_rhs_vars[lhs_buffer_masks[iter->var.get()]];
1974 std::copy_if(
1975 rhs_candidates.begin(), rhs_candidates.end(),
1976 std::inserter(potential_mappings, potential_mappings.begin()),
1977 [&](const Var& var) { return rhs_var_iter_type.at(var.get()) == iter->iter_type; });
1978 }
1979 }
1980
1981 Array<IndexMap> ProposeAllFuseMapping() {
1982 // Now we have calcuated potential mapping for each iter var on LHS. For iters on LHS mapped to
1983 // the same iter on RHS, they will be fused in the original order in LHS block iters. We will
1984 // generate IndexMap to represent such fusion on LHS. For example, if n, h, w on LHS are mapped
1985 // to the same iter var on RHS, we will produce index map `lambda n, h, w: fuse(n, h, w)`, where
1986 // fuse(v0, .., vn) = ((v0 * v1_extent + v1) + ... ) * vn_extent + vn
1987
1988 // the parameters of the result index map, each parameter corresponds to a LHS iter
1989 Array<Var> index_map_src;
1990 // the outputs of the result index map
1991 Array<PrimExpr> index_map_tgt;
1992
1993 // Step 1: Collect extents of LHS iters and prepare the initial indices of the IndexMap
1994 Map<Var, PrimExpr> lhs_iter_extents;
1995 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->lhs_iters_) {
1996 lhs_iter_extents.Set(iter->var, iter->dom->extent);
1997 index_map_src.push_back(iter->var.copy_with_suffix(""));
1998 }
1999
2000 // Step 2: Each iter on RHS has a group of corresponding iters on LHS. Initialize the fusion
2001 // result for each group of iters on LHS.
2002 Map<Var, PrimExpr> fused_lhs_iters;
2003 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
2004 fused_lhs_iters.Set(iter->var, 0);
2005 }
2006
2007 // Step 3: Fuse LHS iters mapped to the same RHS iter
2008 std::unordered_set<Var, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> used_rhs_vars;
2009 for (size_t i = 0; i < extractor_->lhs_iters_.size(); ++i) {
2010 const Var& lhs_iter_var = extractor_->lhs_iters_[i]->var;
2011 const VarSet& rhs_candidates = lhs_feasible_vars_[lhs_iter_var];
2012 if (rhs_candidates.empty()) {
2013 // put unmapped iters at the beginning
2014 index_map_tgt.push_back(index_map_src[i]);
2015 } else if (rhs_candidates.size() == 1) {
2016 Var rhs_var = *rhs_candidates.begin();
2017 PrimExpr fused_lhs = fused_lhs_iters.at(rhs_var);
2018 PrimExpr updated_fused_lhs =
2019 fused_lhs * lhs_iter_extents.at(lhs_iter_var) + index_map_src[i];
2020 fused_lhs_iters.Set(rhs_var, updated_fused_lhs);
2021 used_rhs_vars.insert(rhs_var);
2022 } else {
2023 // non-unique mapping is not supported
2024 return {};
2025 }
2026 }
2027 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
2028 if (!used_rhs_vars.count(iter->var)) {
2029 return {};
2030 }
2031 index_map_tgt.push_back(analyzer_->Simplify(fused_lhs_iters[iter->var]));
2032 }
2033 // At most one mapping is supported.
2034 return {IndexMap(index_map_src, index_map_tgt)};
2035 }
2036
2037 private:
2038 // The extractor that has extracted information for auto tensorization from the workload and the
2039 // tensor intrin.
2040 const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor_;
2041 // The arithmetic analyzer.
2042 arith::Analyzer* analyzer_;
2043 /*! \brief Potential mappings on RHS for each variable on LHS */
2044 std::unordered_map<Var, VarSet, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> lhs_feasible_vars_;
2045};
2046
2047bool CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(const ScheduleState& state, const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
2048 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func,
2049 AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor) {
2050 // Step 1. Analyze desc_func, extract its block, loops and loop vars
2051 // Step 2. Check if `desc_block` matches `block`
2052 // Ignore the scope of buffers when comparing, since we can do cache_read/write
2053 const BlockRealize& block = tir::GetBlockRealize(state, block_sref);
2054 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
2055 auto desc_info = tir::ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(&analyzer, desc_func);
2056
2057 return extractor->VisitStmt(block->block, desc_info.desc_block->block);
2058}
2059
2060bool CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(const tir::Schedule& sch, const tir::BlockRV& block_rv,
2061 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2062 AutoTensorizeComparator extractor(sch->state()->mod);
2063 return CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(sch->state(), sch->GetSRef(block_rv), desc_func, &extractor);
2064}
2065
2066Optional<AutoTensorizeMappingInfo> GetAutoTensorizeMappingInfo(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
2067 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
2068 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2069 AutoTensorizeComparator extractor(self->mod);
2070 if (!CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(self, block_sref, desc_func, &extractor)) {
2071 return NullOpt;
2072 }
2073 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
2074 Array<IndexMap> mappings = AutoTensorizeMappingProposer::ProposeMappings(&extractor, &analyzer);
2075 if (mappings.empty()) {
2076 return NullOpt;
2077 }
2078 ObjectPtr<AutoTensorizeMappingInfoNode> ret = make_object<AutoTensorizeMappingInfoNode>();
2079 ret->mappings = std::move(mappings);
2080 ret->lhs_buffer_map = std::move(extractor.lhs_buffer_map_);
2081 ret->rhs_buffer_indices = std::move(extractor.rhs_buffer_indices_map_);
2082 ret->lhs_iters = std::move(extractor.lhs_iters_);
2083 ret->rhs_iters = std::move(extractor.rhs_iters_);
2084 return AutoTensorizeMappingInfo(ret);
2085}
